# JS Direct App (JSDA)

Mostly tongue-in-cheek proof of concept for direct JS multiplatform graphics drawing. Connects JerryScript with SDL.

Don't bother fuzzing or reporting security issues, there was no attempt to avoid boundary / size issues.

Instructions that likely won't be very helpful and are untested:
```
git clone https://github.com/jerryscript-project/jerryscript.git
jerryscript/tools/build.py --builddir=$(pwd)/example_build --cmake-param="-DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$(pwd)/example_install/" --jerry-math ON

# libsdl2:
curl -O https://www.libsdl.org/release/SDL2-2.0.16.tar.gz
tar -xzf SDL2-2.0.16.tar.gz
./configure --prefix THEPREVDIR/libsdl
make -j11
make install
cd ..


export PKG_CONFIG_PATH="$(pwd)/example_install/lib/pkgconfig/:$(pwd)/libsdl/lib/pkgconfig"
# verify with:
# pkg-config --cflags --libs libjerry-core libjerry-port-default libjerry-ext sdl2

gcc jsda.c -o jsda $(pkg-config --cflags --libs libjerry-core libjerry-port-default sdl2) -lm
./jsda # executes jsdatest.js
```



More on https://twitch.tv/SomeCodingGuy
